prompt:
Implement the resume endpoint for users returning to an incomplete wizard.

PRD §14.3 specifies: user can return to the wizard and resume from the current_step stored in onboarding_state.

Acceptance:
- GET /api/v1/onboarding/resume retrieves org's current onboarding state
- Returns {"current_step": N, "completed_steps": [...], "skipped_steps": [...], "started_at": "...", "last_activity_at": "..."}
- If onboarding is complete (current_step >= 6 and all mandatory steps done), return {"status": "complete"}
- If not started (current_step still 1 and no activity), return {"status": "not_started"}
- Otherwise return {"status": "in_progress", ...full state}

Test: RED test verifies resume state is accurate after partial progression.
